  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Motivating and supporting Caritas in Latin America and the Caribbean in their contribution to the SDGs</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is a direct continuation of the project implemented by SELACC in 2018 which aimed at ensuring that Bishops&#x2019; Conferences in Latin America and the Caribbean have knowledge of and are committed to working towards the achievement of SDGs. As a consequence, national Caritas are now more aware of the importance of the 2030 Agenda. Therefore, to continue the work carried out in this previous project, in the next three years (2019-2021) SELACC is hoping to focus on undertaking targeted actions aimed at contributing to the achievement of the SDGs. As a result of the project, the partner envisages that national Caritas in Latin America and the Caribbean will have a clear commitment to join other actors to contribute to the SDG, particularly those related to gender equity, integral human development, integral ecology, food security, eradication of poverty and migration. Initially, SELACC will focus on strengthening national Caritas&#x2019; commitment and motivation in order to move to concrete actions later on in the project. An important element of the project will be taking advantage of the first round of country evaluations (Voluntary National Reviews) that the governments present to the UN on their countries&#x2019; progress on the achievement of the SDGs. The partner plans to contribute to ensuring that the VNRs are as accurate as possible and that the development policies of the relevant countries truly respond to the fundamental needs of the most disadvantaged. The partner envisages that at the end of this three-year project, a vast majority of national Caritas will have carried out specific advocacy actions aimed at contributing to the achievement of the SGDs.</narrative>
  </description>
